Roof Deck Preparation Checklist¹

Stone‑coated steel panels demand a flat, dry, and structurally sound substrate. Follow these steps before underlayment goes down.

1  Structural Verification
	•	Decking material: 15/32″ APA plywood or 7⁄16″ OSB min (per IRC R803).
	•	Fastener pull‑out: ≥ 90 lb for nails; re‑nail loose sheathing.
	•	Deflection: ≤ 1/240 span (check sagging rafters).

2  Moisture & Damage Survey
	•	Replace any panel with >20 % rot or moisture >16 % (ASTM D4442 meter).
	•	Remove previous felt / debris; vacuum or blow clean.
	•	Repair raised nails or backing‑out screws that could puncture underlayment.

3  Surface Flatness
	•	Tolerance: ±¼″ in 10 ft—shim low spots, plane high edges.
	•	Reroof‑over‑shingles? Allowed only if 1 layer, class A/B, lies flat, & local code permits; TDI windstorm requires full tear‑off in coastal counties.²

4  Batten vs. Direct‑to‑Deck³

Method	Pros	Cons	Texas Fit
Direct‑deck	Max wind uplift, low profile	Less ventilation	Zone 3 coast & high wind belts
2×2 battens	Ventilated air gap lowers attic temps 8‑12 °F	Extra labour; uplift layer	Inland / energy‑code retrofits

graph LR
    A[Deck] -->|optional| B[Battens]
    B --> C[Underlayment]
    C --> D[Panel]

5  Metal Contact Readiness
	•	Remove copper plumbing flashings (galvanic risk).
	•	Prime any exposed steel hardware with zinc‑rich primer.

Common Pitfalls & Fixes

Mistake	Consequence	Prevention
Install over wet deck	Traps moisture → mould	Verify <16 % MC
Uneven sheathing joints	Panel oil‑canning	Plane / shim
Overlay on curled shingles	Fastener back‑out, leaks	Full tear‑off



